abstract: Officials pointed to materials the suspects stockpiled, including explosives; their Middle East travels; and evidence of contacts with people with Islamist extremist views.
snippet: Officials pointed to materials the suspects stockpiled, including explosives; their Middle East travels; and evidence of contacts with people with Islamist extremist views.
lead_paragraph: SAN BERNARDINO, Calif. — The couple who the police say killed 14 people and left 21 wounded here had stockpiled thousands of rounds of ammunition and a dozen homemade pipe bombs in their home, officials said Thursday, a sign that they might have been planning further attacks.

abstract: The suspects, Syed Farook and Tashfeen Malik, were killed after a shooting at a social services center. Family members said the two were married.
snippet: The suspects, Syed Farook and Tashfeen Malik, were killed after a shooting at a social services center. Family members said the two were married.
lead_paragraph: SAN BERNARDINO, Calif. — A heavily armed man and woman terrorized this city on Wednesday, killing at least 14 people and wounding at least 17 at a social services center before leading the police on a manhunt culminating in a shootout that left the two suspects dead, the authorities said.

abstract: Many of this season’s books celebrate gardens that have been protected by trusts, in a few cases for generations.
snippet: Many of this season’s books celebrate gardens that have been protected by trusts, in a few cases for generations.
lead_paragraph: Surely the planting of gardens shares kinship with the making of sand mandalas, those vibrant patterns, painstakingly laid down by Tibetan Buddhist monks over long, backbreaking days only to be ritualistically brushed away when they’re completed. Life is ephemeral; we are in eternal transit. Every dawn, gardeners the world over stroll outside, view the depredations of the night’s creatures and learn to accept impermanence. Gardens are among the most evanescent of our arts. But we dig in anyway, making what we can of our plots — and resisting any thought of their unmaking.

abstract: Tapping some Democratic strategies, the Libre Initiative seeks to win over Hispanics by promoting economic freedom and smaller-government principles.
snippet: Tapping some Democratic strategies, the Libre Initiative seeks to win over Hispanics by promoting economic freedom and smaller-government principles.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — The crowd that lined up around a megachurch here last week — largely Hispanic and mostly poor — came for the Saturday services, but also for the free flu shots that were being offered in the church, and for the Thanksgiving turkeys being given away just outside.

abstract: As a surgeon, Dr. Carson was praised for his dedication and attention to detail, but as a candidate, he has sometimes seemed imprecise or ill informed.
snippet: As a surgeon, Dr. Carson was praised for his dedication and attention to detail, but as a candidate, he has sometimes seemed imprecise or ill informed.
lead_paragraph: When he was not in the operating room at Johns Hopkins Hospital, performing one of his 400 surgeries a year, Dr. Ben Carson could often be seen walking slowly through the hallways, hands behind his back, nodding, smiling and speaking softly to co-workers and students who approached.
